library(ggplot2)
library(dplyr)
library(patchwork)

# Function to plot variables dynamically
plot_vars = function(var_name) {
  bar_plot <- scores_df |> 
    ggplot(aes(x = !!sym(var_name))) +
    geom_bar(fill = "blue", color = "black", alpha = 0.7) +
    labs(x = var_name, y = "Count", title = paste("Bar Plot of", var_name)) +
    theme_minimal()
  
  boxplot = scores_df |> 
    ggplot(aes(x = factor(1), y = !!sym(var_name))) +  # Reference `var_name` as y-axis
    geom_boxplot(fill = "orange", color = "black") +
    labs(x = NULL, y = var_name, title = paste("Boxplot of", var_name)) +
    theme(axis.text.x = element_blank(), axis.ticks.x = element_blank())
  
  # Combine the histogram and boxplot into a single output
  bar_plot / boxplot
}

for (col in names(scores_df)) {
  print(plot_vars(sym(col)))  # Use `sym()` to dynamically reference column names
}
